+# GitHub webhook delivery processing
+
+## Setup and test command
+
+```bash
+bash .shipd/public/setup.sh
+. .venv/bin/activate
+python -m pytest tests/test_github_webhook.py -q
+```
+
+Expected result: all 20 public tests pass without network access.
+
+## Implemented behavior
+
+- Verifies the exact raw webhook body against every configured rotating secret using canonical
+  `X-Hub-Signature-256` HMAC-SHA256 values and constant-time digest comparison.
+- Decodes strict UTF-8 JSON while rejecting duplicate keys, non-finite numbers, non-object
+  payloads, invalid schemas, and excessive nesting.
+- Normalizes `push`, `pull_request`, and `merge_group` deliveries into the stable CI event model.
+- Applies repository, ref, sender, fork, draft, deletion, merge-queue, and skip-CI policy rules.
+- Uses an atomic bounded replay cache with in-progress, committed duplicate, conflict, abort,
+  expiry, and deterministic eviction behavior.
+- Validates case-insensitive request headers, media type, payload size, and canonical delivery
+  UUIDs before returning a `DeliveryResult`.
